      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WITHOUT A TRACE (3) went straight to the front and never headed when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 6th and beaten 7 lengths at Sandown (42.13). Comes out of a solid form race last start. Can atone. FADE TO BLACK (1) has a big motor and ideally suited at the longer trips. Kept coming to finish eighth over 715m at Sandown (42.58) latest in a Special conditions H. Goes very well here at the trip finding the frame in each of four starts. The form out of last race has been strong. Likely to play a prominent role. MEPUNGA LARA (8) was in the minors two back (42.04) at Sandown but ran below best last time there, finishing 7th. The form out of last race has been strong. Key player if finds best. UNIQUE STAR (2) has not raced over this journey but still warrants respect.",
